div.p:
This Kingdom is likened to a grain of mustard seed, for its smal
ness;
to a Pearl, for its Riches, Value and Worth; to Leaven, for its spreading nature: and many other Parables did Christ make use of to discover it by, as to a piece of Silver, which the woman that lost it, lighting the candle, sweeping the house and searching it diligently, at length found it even there where she had lost it.
